      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668502812286-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668502812286-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668502812286-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668502812286-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668502812286-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely, then peel and finely dice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>brown onion[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>(you'll use the rest for later!)</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped mushrooms</strong> and <strong>diced onion </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668502816906-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668502816906-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668502816906-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668502816906-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668502816906-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the<strong> remaining onion </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the mushroom and onion has softened, add them to a bowl (reserve the pan) with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>smoked paprika</strong> (save the rest for later!), your <strong>meat-free burger patties</strong> and<strong> your panko breadcrumbs </strong>and give everything a good mix up until fully combined – this is your <strong>meat-free stroganoff mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668502821632-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668502821632-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668502821632-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668502821632-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668502821632-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>meat-free stroganoff mixture</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and shape into 4 meatballs per person</p><p>Add the<strong> meat-free stroganoff meatballs </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and put it in the oven for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668502825178-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668502825178-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
