          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668502825178-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>sliced mushroom </strong>and cook for an initial 4-5 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Whilst softening, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668502829669-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668502829669-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668502829669-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668502829669-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668502829669-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>remaining smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest for later!) with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> [2 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>creamy single soy </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, stir through the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> – this is your <strong>stroganoff sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668502833774-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668502833774-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668502833774-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668502833774-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668502833774-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 25-30 min, remove the tray from the oven and stir through your <strong>crispy onions</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 2-3 min – these are your<strong> garlic roast potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668502837807-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668502837807-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668502837807-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668502837807-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668502837807-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>meat-free stroganoff meatballs</strong> with the <strong>garlic roast potatoes</strong> to the side and spoon over the <strong>stroganoff sauce</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
